e, England":"Yorkshire, England","Tickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Tickhill, Doncaster, South Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Aldwark, Ecclesfield, West Yorkshire, England":"Aldwark, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Clarell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Clavel  .","Altered form of French   Clavel  .","Catalan: from <i>clavell</i> ‘clove’, earlier also ‘nail’, applied as a metonymic occupational name for a spice trader or a nail maker."],"variants":[{"name":"Clavel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Alfredo, Angel, Bernardina, Carlos, Consuelo, Fernando, Gustavo, Jeronimo, Jorge, Luis, Margarita.  French Andre, Eugenie, Fernande, Jean-Claude, Pierre.","Spanish: from <i>clavel</i> ‘clove’, earlier also ‘nail’, applied as a metonymic occupational name for a spice trader or a nail maker.","French: from Old French <i>clavel</i> ‘bolt (of a door or gate)’ or ‘nail, link, ring (of chain mail)’, used as a metonymic occupational name for a maker or seller. Compare   Clewell  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Clarell was born in 1255, in Tickhill, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William de Clarell III, was 36 and his mother, Johanna, was 23. He married Katherine in 1280, in Aldwark, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1332, in Aldwark, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1255–1332":"1255–1332","1266–1292":"1266–1292","1259–Female":"1259–Surnud","1281–Female":"1281–Surnud","1220–1285":"1220–1285","1232–1292":"1232–1292","1259":"1259","1255":"1255","1332":"1332","1266":"1266","1232":"1232","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1251":"1251","1281":"1281","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Tickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tickhill, Doncaster, South Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aldwark, Ecclesfield, West Yorkshire, England":"Aldwark, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1255–1332":"1255–1332","1266–1292":"1266–1292","1259–Female":"1259–Kuollut","1281–Female":"1281–Kuollut","1220–1285":"1220–1285","1232–1292":"1232–1292","1259":"1259","1255":"1255","1332":"1332","1266":"1266","1232":"1232","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1251":"1251","1281":"1281","1292":"1292","1280":"1280","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Tickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tickhill, Doncaster, South Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Aldwark, Ecclesfield, West Yorkshire, England":"Aldwark, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1255–1332":"1255–1332","1266–1292":"1266–1292","1259–Female":"1259–Décédée","1281–Female":"1281–Décédée","1220–1285":"1220–1285